- TanStack Table for tables (positions, orders, journal, expenses) (same ecosystem as TanStack Query) :contentReference[oaicite:3]{index=3}
- TradingView Lightweight Charts for price charts (fast, small, client-side) :contentReference[oaicite:4]{index=4}

### API + backend
- Next.js Route Handlers / Server Actions (single codebase) :contentReference[oaicite:5]{index=5}
- Auth.js (Next.js integration) :contentReference[oaicite:6]{index=6}

### Data + storage
- PostgreSQL as system-of-record (assets, trades, expenses)
- TimescaleDB extension for time-series (prices, equity curve, metrics) :contentReference[oaicite:7]{index=7}
- Prisma ORM (type-safe DB access + migrations) :contentReference[oaicite:8]{index=8}
  - Alternative: Drizzle ORM (lightweight, SQL-forward) :contentReference[oaicite:9]{index=9}

### Integrations (optional, pick what you actually use)
- Plaid for bank transactions + categorization pipeline :contentReference[oaicite:10]{index=10}
- CCXT for multi-exchange crypto market data / balances (if needed) :contentReference[oaicite:11]{index=11}
- Alpaca for equities market data / account/order updates (if used) :contentReference[oaicite:12]{index=12}

### Jobs + realtime
- Background jobs: BullMQ + Redis (imports, sync, refreshes, recalc) (standard queue pattern; Redis required)
- Realtime: WebSocket streams where supported (market data, order updates) :contentReference[oaicite:13]{index=13}

### Observability
- Sentry for errors + performance tracing :contentReference[oaicite:14]{index=14}
- OpenTelemetry for vendor-neutral traces/metrics :contentReference[oaicite:15]{index=15}
- PostHog for product analytics (events, funnels, feature flags if needed) :contentReference[oaicite:16]{index=16}

### Testing (baseline)
- Unit: Vitest
- E2E: Playwright

### Deployment (simple default)
- Web: Vercel
- DB: managed Postgres + Timescale support (provider-dependent)
- Secrets: environment variables + encrypted secrets store

